# Feature Status

Read-only command. Shows the complete pipeline state of all features.

## Workflow

1. Read `knowledge/wiki/index.md`
2. Read all feature files in `knowledge/wiki/features/`
3. Read `knowledge/intake/quarantined/` for pending conflicts

## Output format

```
## Pipeline

raw (N)             F-XXX — [title] | owner: po
specified (N)       F-XXX — [title] | owner: po | open questions: N | board: pending
ready-for-design    F-XXX — [title] | owner: designer | board: done
in-design (N)       F-XXX — [title] | owner: designer
ready-for-dev (N)   F-XXX — [title] | owner: dev | platforms: [list] | board: done
in-dev (N)          F-XXX — [title] | owner: dev
done (N)            F-XXX — [title]

## Open questions by role
### PO
- F-XXX — [question text]

### Designer
- F-XXX — [question text]

### Developer
- F-XXX — [question text]

## Quarantine backlog
- [folder-name] — [conflict summary]

## Board reviews pending
- F-XXX — [title] [status] — board review not yet run
```

## Notes

- Do not modify any wiki files. This is a read-only operation.
- If there are no open questions for a role, omit that section.
- If the quarantine backlog is empty, state "No quarantined items."
